Subject: Neal Stephenson’s Metaverse - Science Fiction, or near Reality?
Description: In Stephenson’s Snow Crash (which was written in 1992, mind you!) the Metaverse was a futuristic version of the internet based on virtual reality, augmentations, cryptocurrencies, and corporations run amok. Individually, these themes are all very relevant and very real — but are we on the way to alternate realities powered by these emerging techs? What could the future look like? Did Neal Stephenson get it right more than 20 years ago?  Speakers include:Amal Graafstra, Jared Ficklin, Ed Mason, Cynthia Chestek - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Independent SW/HW: Bucking Big Industry for Fun and Profit
Description: Sure, there are juggernauts in software and hardware industry, but if you want to do it yourself, what kinds of challenges are you going to run into?  Come listen to our panelists talk about their experiences with going against the grain as independent software and hardware producers.    Speakers include:Aral Balkan, Ed Mason, Jason Kridner - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Science Fiction is Now Science Reality
Description: Science fiction authors have been writing about futuristic concepts for longer than any of us can remember.  Moore's law, though, has us flying into the future at speeds faster than what any of us have previously comprehended.  Things only imagined by creative minds are coming to reality in exciting, and sometimes terrifying ways.  Come join some authors and technologists as they talk about science fiction themes that are now a reality and what's coming next!  Speakers include:Annalee Newitz, Ed Mason, Karl Schroeder, Charlie Jane Anders, Jen Haeger - Track: Science, Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
